From f744b895ccbfa18a6aef522542dda1d178be03d8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ime <ime@example.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 20:16:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add Japanese (romaji-to-kana) IME
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds an on-device Japanese input method using Wapuro romaji conversion.
Output is pure kana (hiragana or katakana, toggleable). Coverage matches
mainstream IMEs (Mozc, Microsoft IME) for the romaji surface — no
kana-to-kanji conversion (which would need a multi-MB dictionary).

Activated when the build sets -DJP_IME=1. Long-press ESC then cycles:
  EN -> CN -> あ (hiragana) -> ア (katakana) -> EN

New files:
  src/graphics/JapaneseIME.{h,cpp}  ~180-entry romaji table + greedy
                                    converter with proper n-lookahead
                                    and m+b/p assimilation rules.

Modified:
  src/graphics/VirtualKeyboard.{h,cpp}
    - imeLang state field
    - 4-state toggleIME cycle
    - JP-mode branch in insertCharacter (greedy convert on every keystroke)
    - finalize pending tail in submitText (so 'kon'+ENTER -> こん)
    - skip CN candidate panel when in JP mode
    - ESC label shows EN/CN/あ/ア

All 63 unit tests pass (test_japanese_ime.cpp in the patch series).
